#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:5
msgid "$$ \\sqrt{|X \\setminus Y| + |Y \\setminus X| - 2 \\sum_j \\sqrt{\\lambda_j}} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:9
msgid "CMD-distance"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:10
msgid "canonical measure of distance"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:14
msgid "Let $X, Y$ be two data sets, and let $\\lambda_j$ be the eigenvalues of the symmetrized cross-correlation matrix $C\\_{X \\setminus Y, Y \\setminus X} \\times C\\_{Y \\setminus X, X \\setminus Y}$. The model distance is a distance on ${0, 1}^n$. The **CMD-distance** is $\\sqrt{|X| + |Y| - 2 \\sum_j \\sqrt{\\lambda_j}}$, where $\\lambda_j$ are the nonzero eigenvalues of the cross-correlation matrix $C\\_{XY} \\times C\\_{YX}$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:18
msgid "[Todeschini, 2004](https://doi.org/10.1002/9783527613106 \"Consensus Models in Chemistry\")"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/ModelDistance.md:19
msgid "[Todeschini _et al._, 2009](https://doi.org/10.1002/minf.200900004 \"CMD: A New Canonical Measure of Distance\")"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/MountfordSimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{2|X \\cap Y|}{|X||Y \\setminus X| + |Y||X \\setminus Y|} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/MountfordSimilarity.md:9
msgid "The Mountford similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/MountfordSimilarity.md:13
msgid "[Mountford, 1962](https://doi.org/10.2307/2257441 \"An Index of Similarity and its Application to Classificatory Problems\")"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/PatternDifference.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{4|X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}{n^2} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/PatternDifference.md:9
msgid "The pattern difference is a distance on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/PearsonPhiSimilarity.md:1
msgid "Pearson $\\phi$ similarity"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/PearsonPhiSimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}| - |X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}{\\sqrt{|X| \\cdot |\\overline{X}| \\cdot |Y| \\cdot |\\overline{Y}|}} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/PearsonPhiSimilarity.md:9
msgid "The Pearson $\\phi$ similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/Q_0Difference.md:1
msgid "$Q_0$-difference"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/Q_0Difference.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{|X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}|} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/Q_0Difference.md:9
msgid "The $Q_0$-difference is a distance on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RandSimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ 1 - \\frac{|X \\Delta Y|}{n} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RandSimilarity.md:9
msgid "Sokal–Michener's simple matching"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RandSimilarity.md:13
msgid "The Rand similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$. Its square root is called the Euclidean similarity. The corresponding metric $\\frac{|X \\Delta Y|}{n}$ is called the variance or Manhattan similarity."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RogerTanimotoSimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{|\\overline{X \\Delta Y}|}{n + |X \\Delta Y|} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RogerTanimotoSimilarity.md:9
msgid "The Roger–Tanimoto similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RogerTanimotoSimilarity.md:13
msgid "[Rogers and Tanimoto, 1960](https://doi.org/10.1126/science.132.3434.1115 \"A Computer Program for Classifying Plants\")"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RusselRaoSimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{|X \\cap Y|}{n} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/RusselRaoSimilarity.md:9
msgid "The Russel–Rao similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/SokalSneathSimilarities.md:7
msgid "The Sokal–Sneath similarities 1, 2, 3 are similarities on ${0, 1}^n$ defined by $\\frac{2|\\overline{X \\Delta Y}|}{n + |\\overline{X \\Delta Y}|}$, $\\frac{|X \\cap Y|}{|X \\cup Y| + |X \\Delta Y|}$, and $\\frac{|\\overline{X \\Delta Y}|}{|X \\Delta Y|}$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/TverskySimilarity.md:5
msgid "$$ \\frac{|X \\cap Y|}{a|X \\Delta Y| + b|X \\cap Y|} $$"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/TverskySimilarity.md:9
msgid "The Tversky similarity is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$. It becomes the Tanimoto, Sørensen and Kulczynsky 1 similarities for $(a, b) = (1, 1)$, $(\\frac{1}{2}, 1)$ and $(1, 0)$, respectively."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/YuleSimilarities.md:7
msgid "Yule Q similarity"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/YuleSimilarities.md:8
msgid "Yule Y similarity of colligation"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/YuleSimilarities.md:12
msgid "The **Yule Q similarity** is a similarity on ${0, 1}^n$ defined by $\\frac{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}| - |X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}| + |X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}$. The **Yule Y similarity of colligation** is defined by $\\frac{\\sqrt{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}|} - \\sqrt{|X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}}{\\sqrt{|X \\cap Y| \\cdot |\\overline{X \\cup Y}|} + \\sqrt{|X \\setminus Y| \\cdot |Y \\setminus X|}}$."
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/YuleSimilarities.md:16
msgid "[Yule, 1900](https://doi.org/10.1098/rsta.1900.0015 \"On the Association of Attributes in Statistics\")"
msgstr ""

#: src/Distances/DataAnalysis/Binary/YuleSimilarities.md:17
msgid "[Yule, 1912](https://doi.org/10.2307/2340126 \"On the Methods of Measuring Association Between Two Attributes\")"
msgstr ""

